## Compensation Design

Every saga step that can succeed must have a compensating transaction that can undo it:

| Forward Step | Compensating Step |
|---|---|
| `ReserveInventory` | `ReleaseInventory` |
| `ChargePayment` | `RefundPayment` |
| `CreateShipment` | `CancelShipment` |
| `SendConfirmationEmail` | *(not compensable — use correction email instead)* |

### Compensation must be:
- **Idempotent** — can be called multiple times safely
- **Non-failing** — should not throw exceptions (log + alert instead)
- **Eventually executed** — retry until success, use dead letter queue for permanent failures

```java
// Compensation step — idempotent
public void releaseInventory(String orderId) {
    Optional<Reservation> res = reservationRepo.findByOrderId(orderId);
    if (res.isEmpty()) {
        log.info("Inventory already released for order {}", orderId);
        return; // idempotent — already done
    }
    inventoryService.release(res.get().getProductId(), res.get().getQuantity());
    reservationRepo.delete(res.get());
}
```

## Implementing with Temporal

Temporal is a workflow engine that handles saga state persistence, retries, and compensation automatically:

```java
// Temporal Workflow — Saga as code
@WorkflowInterface
public interface OrderSaga {
    @WorkflowMethod
    OrderResult execute(PlaceOrderCommand cmd);
}

public class OrderSagaImpl implements OrderSaga {

    private final InventoryActivity inventory = 
        Workflow.newActivityStub(InventoryActivity.class, options);
    private final PaymentActivity payment = 
        Workflow.newActivityStub(PaymentActivity.class, options);

    @Override
    public OrderResult execute(PlaceOrderCommand cmd) {
        String reservationId = null;
        try {
            // Forward steps
            reservationId = inventory.reserve(cmd.getItems());
            String paymentId = payment.charge(cmd.getPaymentMethod(), cmd.getTotal());
            return OrderResult.success(paymentId);

        } catch (InventoryException e) {
            return OrderResult.failed("Inventory unavailable");

        } catch (PaymentException e) {
            // Compensate
            if (reservationId != null) {
                inventory.release(reservationId); // automatic retry by Temporal
            }
            return OrderResult.failed("Payment declined");
        }
    }
}
// Temporal automatically persists workflow state — survives crashes!
```
